aluation of intangibles Exercises substantial independent judgment in methods, techniques and evaluation criteria for obtaining results Creates formal networks involving coordination among groups Demonstrates creative, innovative approaches and solutions to contractual issues and problems utilizing substantial decision-making skills Acts independently to determine methods and procedures on new or special assignments May provide work direction to other employees as team/project leader or mentor Contributes to shaping major market opportunities Substantial knowledge of applicable federal regulations (FAR/DFARS) and contracting experience with Prime Contractors as wells as all contract types Possesses substantial experience reviewing and analyzing contractual documents for accuracy, performance risk, and conformance with contract terms, conditions, and other provisions Demonstrates excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to deal effectively with personnel at all levels. This includes the ability to communicate effectively with virtually with program teams which are geographically disbursed Exhibits substantial evidence of successful project leadership capabilities with strong analytical/critical thinking skills Demonstrates substantial attention to detail and research skills Is able to prioritize/re-prioritize with changing goals Demonstrates a substantial ability to initiate and successfully implement new ideas that increase organizational efficiency and support business objectives Is self-motivated and able to exercise prudent business judgment in matters of business importance. Collaborates and works effectively cross-functionally throughout the business Possesses substantial computer skills (e.g., Microsoft Office) to support communications and business needs Ability to effectively interface with at the executive levels PREFERRED DEGREE TYPES AND EXPERIENCE: Experience with Intelligence Community customers and multiple contract types, such